<br>
Daylight breaks and mammoths roam, their tusks valuable and thier hides as armor. My group of men were chosen to kill today so the women could make some new cloaks and leggings. We unsheathe our swords and charge at a small male, we slash him to the bone and cut his tusks off and skin him. We stop when we hear the sound of a mad mammoth charging. We turn to look but are too late, He swings his mighty tusks to the side and knock half of us down. I stand next to a man and try to push him away but are to late he is impaled and im thrown into a icy hill. I look up to see injured men running back to our village and a man fall down, I look away as the mammoth rears up and a loud crunch and a dead shriek rings out. I limp to my village to see our children trampled and houses crumpled. Our finest warriors tried to slay the beast but are unsuccessful, it kills all of them and leaves few alive enough to breath. Some men are left hanging from roofs and others crushed. The elder of the village screamed one word that i could understand, &quot;Shadowhide&quot;. The legendary mammoth that could not be killed by any weapon but one forged in the fires of Velious, Made with Blackened alloy and velium melted together and shaped into the head of a spear. The shaft made of black iron and cooled with the blood of a virgin elf. The weapon i must avenge my brothers with seemed so far and as i look upon the beast the more i am angered into killing it. I grab what remained of my blackened alloy armor and walk out upon the ice of Everfrost to reach the Dwarfs in kaladim.<br>
<br>
I walked to a small caves that stunk of gnolls, it could only be the way to Black Burrow. Home of the gnolls and thier canine ways, i walk near the entrance and hail the nearest gnoll. It turns and howls to warn the others. I swing my sword and do not wish to kill it because my father said never kill anythign that you dont want to eat.....I wish the mammoth had known this. I slice thier legs to make them unable to follow and rush through Black burrow to Qeynos hills and run faster as i had half the whole area of Black burrow following me. I see a guard and wish him well as i rush by and hear a lound shout and a dogs screech. I find my way to the karanas to only see what many had told tails about from my homelands, a vast streach of grass and and dirt. I walk for hours on end to reach the other side, lions and griffons attack and beetles eating the remains of other dead beings. I finally come across a large group of spires and a woman inside of it. She was chanting a strange song. I walk up to her and hail her, she turns and stares at me for a second then looks away. She continued her chanting, I asked her if she was a wizard who could take me to Kaladim and the dwarfs. She stoped her chanting and shouted that she was busy and if i disturbed her again she would send me to my eternal grave in hell. Since i was never good at dieing i pulled out my sword and slashed at her for her threat. She blocked my blow with magic and stunned me, then she walked around me saying things in a unknown tongue. I assumed from what i had learned that she was a dark elf, and that she was thinking of a way to rob me and cast me into a different world. I felt like this was the end and i would never be able to avenge me village and kill &quot;Shadowhide&quot;. Then with some strange inner strength i felt the binding come loose and swong with all my might at the dark elf. I sliced the pendant around her neck and was thrown backwards into the grasslands, that was a mistake i guess. I was knocked out and awoke to a darkness, i rolled over and saw a gypsie camp and thier fire breaking the darkness.<br>
I walked near and hailed their leader.<br>
<br>
They sat me down and asked why i was out here in the middle of nowhere. I told them my tale and they all fell silent, then one said she might be able to help me shorten my journey. She pulled out some blackened alloy and iron. she placed them in a bag and handed in to me, I thought it would be as heavy as a mammoth tusk but was light as a gnoll paw. I thanked her and asked if this was all till i saw what she pulled out next. She pulled out a flask of glowing liquid, crimson in color and bright as a willowisp. She told me it was the blood of the Virgin Elf Gypsie Princess, Elftear. I felt guilty about taking it but thanked her. They then said some magical words and i felt as if i was thrown into a black pit. I fell for what seemed like minutes and landed in a mountain range that i could only assume was Butcher Block. I stood up and saw a goblin holding the Princess's blood. I yelled at him to give it back but he ran off into a mountain. I followed him in and finally caught up with him, I slashed at him and connected with his wrist. He shrieked and threw the flask into the air, I dove to catch it adn slid deeper into the cave. I finally stopped and held up the flask triumphant. I turned around and was near the exit when a bandit shoved a dagger into my back. I felt a sharp pain of thousands of needles and turned around to see a dwarf. he slashed at me again and i stopped the blade with my chainmail gloved hand. I yanked the dagger away from him and pinned him to the ground. I said that father always proclaimed dwarf tasted good and stabbed his dagger through his throat and kicked him rolling down the cave, I stood till i heard a muffed thump and a crack of bones.  I continued on to kaladim nursing my wound on my back. i felt weaker and weaker as i continued on. Finally i saw the entrance to Kaladim. i rushed in and said hello, the guards then took my to thier leader and king, but that is a later story. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% 