as i entered the kings Throne room i looked back and saw a red strem and wondered if that could be me. I looked back to the king and realized i was no longer standing but being held up by the guards. The king spoke out of the bravery i expressed by entering his kingdom after slaying the glorified bandit Gundl and his friend 6 Fingers the goblin. I tried to speak back about my quest but i could not make a sound with my voice. Finally the king noticing the wound i had (Like the red stream wasnt enough) he ordered me to the cleric guild for healing. I passed out halfway there and woke up later to a bearded woman standing over me. I let out a whisper and asked how long i had been out. She replied i had been out for 3 days and they thought i wouldnt make it so the had etched a gravestone reading &quot;Loud Mouthed Stranger who stained our floors with his blood after the mighty battle between He and the bandit Gundl&quot;. I smiled weakly at the stone and said my name was Uluian of the Guild Ninja Bard. She replied he name being Halfpent. I spent 4 more days in Kaladim before they replied to help me on my quest. They sent me out on one last mission of killing the two ogres Cornflunk and Zarchoomi. As a reward for slaying Gundl they gave me a old blade of the last man to see them. I immediately noticed that it had not gained rust and weighed much less then my sword. So i set out to kill the two ogres, I figured it would not be too hard considering their size. I thought they may have left the mountains, but things always happen to be bad at the best of times. A giant man that looked deformed and half the size of a normal giant had jumped from a 50 foot cliff and landed infront of me. He spoke a slured speech and the best i could make of it was I am Cornflunk, you have trespassed on Greenblood land and shall die for destroying his lands. I spoke back with I had never seen his lands nor touched them, I was Uluian the last of the Ninja Bards and must slay him to avenge my Tribal Honor. He was extremely fast for his size and had hit me before i could step aside. His punch felt like a Mammoth crushing my rib cage with its foot. I fell backwards a few feet and didnt have time to grasp my aching chest because a 300 pound man had leaped to kill me. I rolled aside to find a female ogre standing there with a spell being casted. I unsheathed my newly won blade and cut her leg in hopes of stoping her. One the blade and touched her flesh and torn through it i felt a rush of power and lept up onto my feet. Nothing could prepare me for what happen next. A fully grown female ogre let out a bellow so loud it shook the nearby mountains. I felt like my head would explode as the noise kept coming. I screamed my pain but it was only a whisper compared to hers. I felt rage and pain to make her stop and turned around with the blade ready to kill. I let out my rage into a mighty swing and cut her head from her shoulders. Cornflunk who had recovered from his leap had hit me from behind and i felt his words of rage and sorrow as he screamed for his lost friend Zarchoomi and I who had killed her. I felt pain but it was only a bee sting compared to the thought of losing my life on my journey of revenge. I swung at him and we fought for hours, both of us looking to revenge something we loved. We finally reached a beach and were worn out from constant fighting. I knew this was the last chance i had or the last place i would see. I swung my heavying sword like a club and knocked the tired cornflunk into the water. He started splashing and i knew he could not swim from this. I do not know whether it was the hatred from Shadow Hide or memory of him hiting me, but i lept upon him and held his fat head under water till his grasp on me had weakened and fallen away. I waded out from the ocean water and drug my worn out body back to Kaladim to continue on my journey. I felt sorrow for the two ogres but also felt hope that i would be able to put their deaths towards helping the future. The sun was setting and my hopes were rising.<br>
